>poll() isn't allowed to sleep for many reasons. Some are technical. But <br />the most obvious one is that a sleeping "poll()" is totally against the <br />whole point of polling in the first place!<br /><br />So is there some big conceptual reason to change how poll() has always <br />worked?<br /><br />If you worry about debuggability, then we could just add a <br /><br />	preempt_enable();<br />	..<br />	preempt_disable();<br /><br />around the poll calls (purely for catching errors) to get a big warning if <br />somebody tries to call a sleepable function.<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
